The paper deals with object interaction recognition in egocentric video, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses inconsistencies in ground truth annotations, which is a common issue in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for annotating temporal bounds based on a cognitive model, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of state-of-the-art approaches, which could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
